If a phone is selected randomly, then what is the probability that it has a good battery life? (Enter the answer correct to 2 decimal accuracy).

questions.question_text_1: An owner of a television shop sends his repairman to service five televisions on site each day. If the repairman has only one such part, then find the probability that at most one television he services will require installation of this particular part.
